Prince","startTime":null,"eventDescription":"Oakland natives and twin brothers Ambrose and Austin Prince began creating as soon as they could hold an idea in their head for long enough to get it out through words, movements or on to paper.

When the two were kids, creation took place primarily through drawing and playing dress-up (placing underwear on their heads as scuba masks and extra large tube socks on their feet as flippers, pretending to be the great sea explorer Jaques Cousteau). In high school they found outlets in "turf dancing" and running a small custom airbrushing business out of their parents tool shed. In college they began writing and singing songs, and post college they decided to try their hand at photography and video making.

This is the place where all of these passions come together.

Mix the spirited soulfulness of Musiq with the laid-back island vibes of Jack Johnson, and the lyrical rap precision of J. Cole, then add a dash of indie rock from the likes of Cold War Kids and the Black Keys and you have something of the pallet from which The Brothers Prince create their sound.

Getting their start as entertainers in high school during Oakland’s Hyphy movement through “turf dancing,” front men (and identical twins) Ambrose and Austin have continued to pursue their artistic passions through music composition and performance with their latest project, The Brothers Prince.
